.SH NAME
WordListRole::FromArray \- Provide first_word(), next_word(), reset_iterator(), each_word() from _array()
.SH VERSION
.IX Header "VERSION"
This document describes version 0.7.11 of WordListRole::FromArray (from Perl distribution WordList), released on 2021\-09\-26.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This role can be used if you want to construct a dynamic wordlist module from an
array of words. You provide \fB_array()\fR, and this role will provide \f(CWeach_word()\fR,
\&\f(CWfirst_word()\fR, \f(CWnext_word()\fR, \f(CWreset_iterator()\fR.
.SH "REQUIRED METHODS"
.IX Header "REQUIRED METHODS"
.SS _array
.IX Subsection "_array"
Must return an arrayref of words.
.SH "PROVIDED METHODS"
.IX Header "PROVIDED METHODS"
.SS each_word
.IX Subsection "each_word"
.SS first_word
.IX Subsection "first_word"
.SS next_word
.IX Subsection "next_word"
.SS reset_iterator
.IX Subsection "reset_iterator"
